120. A method of preparing a nucleic acid library from a nucleic acid sample, the method comprising:
(a) providing a set of amplification primers comprising:
a plurality of random primers, wherein each random primer comprises a random 3′ portion and a constant 5′ priming portion; and
a plurality of locus specific primers configured to amplify a plurality of predetermined genomic regions;
wherein each plurality of random primers and locus specific primers in the set of amplification primers is a mixture of different primers;
 (b) amplifying the nucleic acid sample using the set of amplification primers to obtain amplified polynucleotides; (c) circularizing the amplified polynucleotides to obtain circular polynucleotides; and (d) amplifying the circular polynucleotides, thereby preparing the nucleic acid library.

